                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/507.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Costa Rican Minister for Foreign Affairs</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d201fn1">Mutatis mutandis to the Ministers for Foreign
                        Affairs of Honduras, Guatemala, Salvador, and Nicaragua.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference of your Government, in telegram to Costa Rican judge of Central
                    American court, to assistance of Government of United States in efforts of the
                    Washington conference culminating in inauguration of court is much appreciated
                    by this Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
